OL,6,FThe cross-party standards committee
OL,7,Fagreed with the commissioner's finding
OL,8,Fthat Davies had breached rules one and
OL,9,Fthree of the code of conduct - members
OL,10,Fmust uphold the overarching
OL,11,Fprinciples, and members must not act
OL,12,For behave in a manner that brings the
OL,13,FSenedd, or its members generally, into
OL,14,Fdisrepute - but did not breach rule
OL,15,Ftwo whereby members must act
OL,16,Ftruthfully because the commissioner
OL,17,Fhad concluded "there was no intention
OL,18,Fto deceive".
